Narrative:
On April [XXX], 2025 at 11:57 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a van on [XXX] near [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was parked at the curb facing southwest on [XXX] when a van parked in front of the Waymo AV reversed and the rear of the van made contact with the front of the stationary Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On April [XXX], 2025 at 12:41 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Venice, California was in a collision involving a van on [XXX] near [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was parked in-lane for a passenger drop-off facing southwest on [XXX] with hazard lights activated. A van that was stopped directly behind the Waymo AV began to maneuver around the stationary Waymo by crossing the yellow center line, entering the opposing lane of travel. As the van proceeded to the left of the stationary Waymo AV, the Waymo AV passenger opened the driver side rear door and the passenger side of the van made contact with the open driver side rear door of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The passengers who were seated in the rear of the Waymo AV and the front passenger seat were not belted at the time of the collision, as they were likely preparing to exit the Waymo AV. Both vehicles sustained damage. 
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because a vehicle involved was towed away. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

As the van passed the parked Waymo AV, the passenger side of the van made contact with the rear driver side of the Waymo AV. The May vehicle was traveling through an intersection with a van in the oncoming left turn lane. As the May vehicle enters the intersection, the van creeps towards its turn.  Predicting that the two will get too close, the May vehicle elects to stop hard. As vehicle is coming to a stop in the stop-hard policy, the turning van fails to respond in time and collides with the rear left corner of the vehicle.
In the new software, deploying within the next month, agent-proximity has been replaced with agent-clearance. Performing resimulations of the incident with the latest branch verifies that this issue does not persist.

On December [XXX], 2023 at 3:51 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in Scottsdale, Arizona was in a collision involving a van on [XXX] at [XXX].
The Waymo AV was stopped for a red light in a dedicated left turn lane on southbound [XXX] at  [XXX], preparing to make a left turn onto eastbound [XXX]. At this intersection, this traffic light had four bulbs, with the bottom-most bulb being both a green and yellow bulb for a protected left sequence. When the bottom bulb turned green for a protected left, the two vehicles in front of the Waymo AV proceeded, and as the Waymo AV approached, the traffic light began to change sequence to become an unprotected left turn, with the green arrow bulb turning to a yellow arrow. The Waymo AV braked and came to a stop past the crosswalk, but before entering the intersection (as defined in Arizona). As the Waymo AV came to a stop, a van approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage, and the passenger in the Waymo AV reported a minor injury. 
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because a vehicle involved was towed away. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("AV"), operating in manual mode, was traveling northbound on [XXX] between [XXX] and [XXX]. The AV operator improperly engaged from manual into autonomous mode while the AV was in motion, temporarily causing the AV to steer to the right.
